node.text: We need to find a way to come together and stop these hate crimes! I’ve spoken up about this a year ago.. when Asians were being attacked because of xenophobia and the idea that they are the cause of Covid.. a year later and here we are still being punished.. this is unfair and unjust.. and flat out EVIL!

node.title: Asian Americans are facing a tragedy that is absolutely heartbreaking

node.text: Morning Meditation! This is a guided meditation by Heidi E. Spear that I frequently listen to to help me feel grounded and to help start my day.. especially when I know I’m gonna have a long productive day. Meditating helps me stay focused, present and relieve stress. It gives me a chance to focus on my breathing and calm my mind, which can be so hard to do sometimes which is why I like to listen to guided meditations. Even if I’m having a stressful moment during the day.. I’ll take a moment to meditate to release tension. Hope this encourages you to incorporate mediation into your daily lives.. it doesn’t have to be this particular meditation or a guided meditation.. you can meditate on your own.. whatever helps you calm the mind 🤎link in bio!
